title: For Sale:  1976 Browning Hi-Power 9mm, Series C, UNFIRED w/original pouch & Browning holster
postcontent: 1976 Browning Belgium Hi-Power, Series C, 9mm unfired and pristine with one original unused mag & Browning black pouch & manual & custom- ordered Browning Holster. In the period this gun was manufactured 40 years ago, FN was sending new Hi-Powers to Browning in plain cardboard boxes. Browning then placed the Hi-Powers in black, “Browning” marked pouches made in the U.S. I have collected Hi-Powers for years and this is the first pouch I have seen with the original Browning white label still attached. This label is hand numbered to the gun. In those days Hi-Powers were sold in the black “Browning” pouch with red lining instead of a box. The holster was custom ordered and purchased by the original owner at the same time he bought the gun. During years 1976 – 1978, Browning offered a special, custom order BHP holster. This custom holster was produced by El Paso Saddlery Company in El Paso, Texas. The holster is lined, basketweave stamped, and bordered, with the Browning logo on both the front and back. The standard Browning Hi-Power holster was unlined, plain, made in Mexico, and was marked as such on the back side. Price: $1,250 FTF. No trades at this time. Buyer must have VA drivers license and sign bill of sale.

postcontent:
For sale is a nice and hard to find Beretta Model 84 .380ACP SA/DA semi-auto pistol, this is the first model/version of the 84.  It comes with the smooth wood grips, plastic grips, 3-13rd. mags(one factory and two Mec-Gar) and a nice DeSantis shoulder holster for the pistol and two extra mags($120 in the DeSantis rig and two extra mags alone).  Date code puts this pistol at 1977, overall, I would say excellent condition especially for a pistol almost 40 years old.  There is just a touch of wear at the front part of the left slide edge.  If you like the 92 models, you will love this one, feels great in the hand and would be great for CCW or OCW in 2016.  I would really like to keep this one, but need to let some go to take care of other projects.
$500 firm in cash for the pistol and mags only or $540 firm with the DeSantis rig, this rig will also work with other small pistols.  Higher in trade value as I am really wanting the cash right now.
Might look at trades as long as it's a good deal, otherwise, I will not be interested as I do not need anything right now.  If offering a trade, please be specific on what you have and what you are offering, straight trade, trade +/- cash or other, so I know the deal.
Trades considered: 
I will consider most firearms, but mostly interested in semi-autos.  Will consider, but less intrested in revolvers, shotguns and bolt-guns.
Will consider several stripped AR-15 and AR-10 lowers for future projects, depending on brand and the value you put on each.  I will also consider complete lowers as well, but I can build quality lowers much cheaper than buying them complete, so the value to me on a complete lower will likely be lower than your value, just a heads-up.  Would also like more Pmags for both.
Ammo in the common calibers 9mm to help complete a deal, .45ACP, .357 Mag, .223/5.56, 7.62x39, .308/7.62x51, 7.62x54.  I have PLENTY, but will consider an all ammo trade if it's really good.
1oz. Silver Eagles, rounds and bars.  Gold in grams.  Please check current prices before making offer.
Again, I am more than covered on everything, but I don't mind trading for more of the same as long as it's a good deal.
Must be legal to own a firearm in TX.  FTF in the Garland area.  Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  RWS DIANA MODEL 24 YOUTH AIR RIFLE .177 cal
postcontent: RWS Diana -Made in Germany. German engineering & quality proven design break action air rifle. I bought this for my son to shoot. He probably didn't put 100 pellets through it. Pellets are less likely to ricochet then BB'S. I think they are safer in general.  It’s been in my gun safe for 14 years. This is a youth model or small frame adult gun. It is pretty much identical to the model 34.  They are capable of 5/16 groups at 30 ft. If you miss it's not the gun. It has a real nice adjustable iron site and a scope rail. It has a 2 stage non-adjustable trigger. It's shoots at 700 fps. It is easier to cock then the model 34 and has a shorter barrel so it's not as fast.  It has a scuff on the stock but overall in really good shape. Break the barrel from the muzzle by pulling on the barrel, it's hinged; load a pellet, close the barrel, flip the safety off and shoot. Reliable, repeatable fun.  These are referred to as springers. They do not store air, a piston is spring loaded when you cock the barrel. Pulling the trigger releases the piston and pushes air through orifices to propel the pellet.   Questions ask for Jim REDACTED. It is perfectly legal to ship this gun ups or whatever both federally and in the state of Wisconsin. I will ship no problem.
